{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641731","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641731"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:30:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:30:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17898"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17898","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17898"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10612"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114647"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10612","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10612"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17898"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96650"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7001"},{"type":"tags","id":"10293"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24730"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24733"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26838"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114647","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114647"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe arcuate nucleus is a critical region in the hypothalamus involved in the regulation of appetite and energy balance. It contains different populations of neurons that either stimulate or inhibit food intake.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following types signal hunger?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sim1/MC4R","NPY/AgRP","POMC/CART","ZdR/Agg3","CRH/AVP"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWithin the arcuate nucleus, \u003Cstrong\u003ENPY/AgRP\u003C/strong\u003E neurons are responsible for signalling hunger. These neurons release neuropeptide Y (NPY) and agouti-related peptide (AgRP), which stimulate appetite and food intake.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESim1/MC4R\u003C/strong\u003E are involved in the regulation of energy expenditure and satiety. \u003Cstrong\u003EPOMC/CART\u003C/strong\u003E neurons promote satiety and reduce food intake. \u003Cstrong\u003EZdR/Agg3\u003C/strong\u003E is not a recognised neuron type in the arcuate nucleus. \u003Cstrong\u003ECRH/AVP\u003C/strong\u003E are involved in stress response and water balance, not directly in hunger signalling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe balance between NPY/AgRP and POMC/CART neurons is crucial for maintaining energy homeostasis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Neuropeptide Y (NPY) and agouti-related peptide (AgRP) neurons in the arcuate nucleus of the hypothalamus are involved in signalling hunger.","The arcuate nucleus contains distinct populations of neurons that regulate appetite and energy balance."],"references":["Hall JE. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2021. Chapter 72; pg. 883.","Bender DA, Cunningham SM. Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press; 2021.","Salway JG. Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons; 2016.","Judge A, Dodd MS. Metabolism. Essays Biochem. 2020 Oct 8;64(4):607-647.","Austin J, Marks D. Hormonal regulators of appetite. Int J Pediatr Endocrinol. 2009;2009:141753.","Hernando-Redondo J, Toloba A, Benaiges D, Salas-Salvad\u00f3 J, Mart\u00ednez-Gonzalez MA, Corella D, et al. Mid- and long-term changes in satiety-related hormones, lipid and glucose metabolism, and inflammation after a Mediterranean diet intervention with the goal of losing weight: A randomized, clinical trial. Front Nutr. 2022 Nov 18;9:950900.","Yeung AY, Tadi P. Physiology, Obesity Neurohormonal Appetite And Satiety Control. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96650"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17898"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96650","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96650"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-18T14:35:23+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-18T14:35:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10612"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114647"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4929"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6d","name":"Endocrine","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+